    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">Fava</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-08-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 15,
                                1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 9th instant, expressing the gratification of
                            the Government of Italy for the presence of two vessels of war of the U.
                            S. Navy at Genoa, on the occasion of the visit of their majesties to the
                            Columbian Exhibition there during September next.</p>
                <p>It has afforded me pleasure to inclose a copy of your note to the
                            Secretary of the Navy.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
